    "problemStatement": "You are given an integer **N**. For each pair of integers (**L**, **R**), where **1** ≤ **L** ≤ **R** ≤ **N** you can find the number of distinct digits that appear in the decimal representation of at least one of the numbers **L L+1** ... **R**.\n\n\nFind the sum of all that numbers. Since the answer can be large, output it modulo **1000000007**.",
